Reading: あっというまに

Meanings:
1. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.); adverb (fukushi)) in an instant; in a flash; in the blink of an eye; in no time at all; just like that

Examples:
1. 休暇はあっという間に終わった。
→ The holiday ended all too soon.

Reading: いけない

Meanings:
1. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.); adjective (keiyoushi)) bad; wrong; naughty
2. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.); adjective (keiyoushi)) must not (do, be); should not; ought not to [after the -te form of a verb or adjective]
3. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.); adjective (keiyoushi)) useless; no good; bad
4. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.); adjective (keiyoushi)) hopeless; beyond hope
5. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.); adjective (keiyoushi)) unfortunate; a shame; a pity [used to express sympathy]
6. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.); adjective (keiyoushi)) unable to drink (alcohol)
7. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.); adjective (keiyoushi)) so as not to ...; so that ... (won't); in case ...; for fear that ...; lest ... [as ...(すると|しては)いけない(から|ので)]

Examples:
1. このフロッピーをフォーマットしてはいけません。
→ You mustn't format this floppy disk.

1. 彼本人は好人物なんだが、その取り巻きがどうもいけないね。
→ I really like him, but not his circle of friends.

Reading: いつもより

Meanings:
1. (adverb (fukushi)) more than usual (word usually written using kana alone)

Examples:
1. わたしはいつもより遅く床に就いた。
→ I went to bed later than usual.

Reading: おのぼりさん

Meanings:
1. (noun (common) (futsuumeishi)) countryside people (in town); visitor from the country; out-of-towner; country bumpkin (visiting the big city); yokel (word usually written using kana alone)

Examples:
1. すこし落ち着け吉祥、おのぼりさん丸出しだぞ。
→ Calm down a little, Kissho, your bumpkin nature is standing out!

Reading: おさきに

Meanings:
1. (adverb (fukushi)) before; previously (polite (teineigo) language)
2. (adverb (fukushi)) ahead (polite (teineigo) language)
3. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.)) pardon me for leaving (before you) (abbreviation; polite (teineigo) language)

Examples:
1. お先にどうぞ。
→ After you.

1. どうぞ、お先に！
→ Go ahead!

Reading: かみさん, カミさん

Meanings:
1. (noun (common) (futsuumeishi)) (one's) wife (word usually written using kana alone)
2. (noun (common) (futsuumeishi)) (someone's) wife
3. (noun (common) (futsuumeishi)) landlady

Examples:
1. うちのかみさんは元プロレスラーで、だからもし私が浮気をしているところを見つかりでもしようものなら、それこそコテンパンにやられてしまうよ。
→ My wife used to be a pro-wrestler, so if she ever catches me two-timing her, I'd be beaten to a pulp.

1. あの詐欺師と金髪のコールガールは下宿のおかみさんを怒らせるには申分のない取り合わせだ。
→ The confidence man and his blonde call girl make a perfect match in enraging his landlady.

Reading: からといって

Meanings:
1. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.)) just because; even if; even though (word usually written using kana alone)

Examples:
1. 他人が悪い事をしているからといって自分もそうしてよいということにはならない。
→ Two wrongs don't make a right.

Reading: そのうえで

Reading: そのあと, そのご, そののち

Examples:
1. その後の話はご存じでしょう。
→ You know the rest of the story.

Reading: そのうえ

Meanings:
1. (conjunction; noun (common) (futsuumeishi); adverb (fukushi)) in addition; furthermore
2. (conjunction; noun (common) (futsuumeishi); adverb (fukushi)) above (which); on top of (which)

Examples:
1. この本はおもしろい、その上、非常にためになる。
→ This book is interesting and, what is more, very instructive.

1. その上さらに５ドル払った。
→ I paid five dollars in addition.

Reading: というのは

Meanings:
1. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.); conjunction) because ...; for ...; the reason being ... (word usually written using kana alone)
2. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.); conjunction) as for ...; when it comes to ...; regarding ...; how about ... (word usually written using kana alone)

Examples:
1. うぬぼれた人というのは自分たちは他人よりも優れているのは当然だと思っている。
→ Conceited people take it for granted that they are superior to others.

1. その本を机の上に戻しておいた方がいいですよ。というのは所有者がそこへ戻ってくるでしょうから。
→ You had better put the book back on the desk, for the owner will come back there.

Reading: ともいう

Meanings:
1. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.)) also called

Reading: といえば

Meanings:
1. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.)) speaking of ... (word usually written using kana alone)
2. (expressions (phrases, clauses, etc.)) when it comes to ...; as for ...; if one were to say ... (word usually written using kana alone)

Examples:
1. 田中さんといえば、最近彼に会ったか。
→ Talking of Mr Tanaka, have you seen him lately?

1. 父は料理が得意だ。母はといえば、食べるのが得意だ。
→ Father is good at cooking. As for Mother, she is good at eating.

Reading: いえる

Examples:
1. その仕事はまだほとんど終わったと言える状態ではない。
→ The job isn't anywhere near done.

Reading: といわれる

Examples:

Reading: どれ

Meanings:

Examples:
1. あなたはそれらのうちのどれを選んでもよい。
→ You may choose any of them.
2. あなたの鞄はどれですか。
→ Which is your bag?

1. 「じつは自由研究で相談したいことがあって・・・」「どれ・・・。ふーん、被子植物について調べてるのね」
→ "Well, there's something I'd like your advice on about my research project ..." "Let's see... Hmm, you're investigating flowering plants then."
